President Donald J. Trump has announced his intention to nominate Claire M. Grady of Pennsylvania as Under Secretary for Management at the Department of Homeland Security. Grady currently serves as the Director of Defense Procurement and Acquisition Policy, where she advises on acquisition and procurement strategies for major weapon systems and information systems programs. She has also held positions in the Coast Guard and the Department of Homeland Security.

Additionally, President Trump has announced his intention to nominate David J. Redl of New York as Assistant Secretary for Communications and Information at the Department of Commerce. Redl is currently the Chief Counsel at the U.S. House of Representatives Committee on Energy and Commerce, where he advises on communications and technology matters. He has also worked on spectrum policy and reducing regulatory mandates at CTIA - The Wireless Association.

President Trump has also announced his intention to designate members of the Board of Directors of the Overseas Private Investment Corporation, although specific individuals have not been named.